      "description": "Two-loop massless planar pentabox with five off-shell external legs of common virtuality $p_i^2=-m^2$ ('tripentagon family'). The specific integral computed is the top-sector in the near mass-shell limit $m \\to 0$, expanded as $\\sum_{l=0}^4 a_l \\log^{4-l}(m^2)$. Method of regions decomposition into 32 nontrivial leading regions, each evaluated by a tropical-geometry-based strategy using Newton polytopes of $U \\cdot F$ and locally finite integrands with parametric integration by HyperInt. Coefficients $a_0,a_1,a_2$ analytic in the paper; $a_3,a_4$ delivered in the ancillary notebook. Cross-checked against FIESTA.",
